data.title: Ella Fitzgerald's Culture and Times
data.text: April 25, 1917 Ella Fitzgerald is born. 1930-1939 The Great Depression 1932 Ella's mother dies. 1934 Ella's stage debut at the Apollo Theater. 1935 Ella meets Chick Webb. 1935 Ella performs at the Savoy ballroom for the first time. November, 1937 Ella is voted number One Female Vocalist. 1939-1945 World War II June 16, 1939 Chick Webb dies. 1940 Ella was invited to Hollywood to sing in a movie Ride 'Em Cowboy. October, 1945 Ella scats on her record for the first time. 1953 Ella begins to create her Songbook collection. 1964 Civil Rights Act passed. Spring, 1965 Ella has an emotional breakdown on stage in Munich, Germany. 1972 Ella is diagnosed with having a cataract, loses vision in one eye. August, 1985 Ella begins to have health problems. June 14, 1996 Ella Fitzgerald dies.
